  "prompt": "Where is the Audi A4 battery located?",
  "response": "The location of the battery in an Audi A4 can vary depending on the model year and specific configuration, but generally, it is found in one of the following locations:\n\n1. **Under the Hood**: In many Audi A4 models, the battery is located in the engine bay, typically on the driver's side (left side in left-hand-drive vehicles) or passenger side (right side in left-hand-drive vehicles). \n\n2. **Trunk/ Luggage Compartment**: In some Audi A4 models, particularly those with all-wheel drive (quattro) or specific engine configurations, the battery is located in the trunk. In these cases, it is usually situated under the floor panel on the right or left side.\n\n3. **Under the Rear Seat**: In a few models, the battery might be located under the rear seat.\n\nTo confirm the exact location for your specific Audi A4, it\u2019s best to consult the owner\u2019s manual or contact an Audi dealership. If you\u2019re looking to access or replace the battery, ensure you follow proper safety procedures, as modern vehicles often have complex electrical systems.",
